Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Description: A brief, simple tutorial, introducing the basic movement and combat controls.
Mission.DescriptionStory:
“Talk to me, Goose.”
Lieutenant Caedmon’s hands shook as she gripped the armrests on her command chair. What had began as simple, even boring guard duty on one of the Empire’s backwater worlds was very quickly turning into something over her pay grade.
“Their lead elements are almost on top of us, Commander,” the AI said, in a tone normally associated with fancy restaurant waiters. “Heavy tank column is another twelve minutes out.”
“And their cloakybots?”
“Based on the direction in which our supply lines are being cut, Commander, I’d say they’re about to finish encircling us.”
“Great.” She pulled her right fingers into a clenched fist. “And you’re sure they’re with the coup? Not the Dynasty or the Libbies?”
“Five nines, ma’am. At a guess, they’re plowing through us on the way to New Warsaw.”
[i]Oh, joy.[/i] She put her face in her hands. [i]And to think I just graduated a year ago. Just how did I manage to get myself into this mess, anyway? I’m only a lieuten-[/i]
“Commander, they’re here!” a Glaive frantically cut in, jerking her from her morose thoughts. “Light vehicles barreling down both passes, ETA two minutes!”
Gritting her teeth, Caedmon took a moment to curse that bastard Major Aethelred and the sweeping political changes that had given him his (entirely undeserved, in her opinion) rank. She’d warned him, told him the defenses were too concentrated to provide adequate coverage of even the fraction of the planet’s surface they were supposed to hold. But of course he wasn’t going to meet any recommendations by a mere mutant, especially one three whole grades below him, with anything other than snide dismissal, was he? Goddamn more-blessed-than-thou purebreds...
Okay. Deep breath. “Recommendation, Goose?”
“The valley to the east is still effectively open, Commander.” Popping the tactical display up on the holo-screen, he highlighted the winding pass, blood red lines constricting on it. “With our current defenses, we should be able to stall their advance more than long enough to reach Extraction Point Oscar safely, as long as we move quickly.”
Her jaw tightened. “I don’t like running away while someone else dies covering my ass.”
“How do you feel about dying uselessly, ma’am?”
[i]Smartass.[/i] “Fine.”
Her thoughts flowed into the machine, and massive command unit came alive with a loud whirr, flexing its actuators. Hot plasma boiled and expanded in the onboard microfusion reactor, energy flowing to motors, sensors and the mech’s lethal energy weapons, glowing with contained fury.
“Let’s go.”

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Get your commander to safety in the east, punching through any opposistion while allied forces hold a delaying action in the rear.
TriggerLogic.Title: Escape to the East

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Hostile forces have cut us off! The enemy is closing in!
We'll hold them off, Commander! Get to safety at the end of the valley to the east!

for i=1,#units do local ud = UnitDefs[Spring.GetUnitDefID(units[i])] if ud.customParams.commtype then unitID = units[i] break end end
WG.EnableUnitHighlight(unitID)

TriggerLogic.Message: The chokepoint up ahead has a considerable enemy presence. We're dropping in some units to assist in punching through.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
You can select multiple units at once by holding down Left Mouse and dragging a box around them.
Selection of a particular unit can be toggled on or off by Ctrl+left clicking the unit.
To move units in formation, hold down the mouse button while issuing the move order and draw the desired formation.
The chokepoint up ahead has a considerable enemy presence. We're dropping in some units to assist in punching through.

Your commander can repair other units. Right-click on the damaged unit, or press R and left-click.
Repairing is twice as fast as building, but units will be repaired 4x slower if they have been damaged in the last ten seconds.
Heads up, Commander! Those Stardusts will cut us to pieces if we try to take them head-on!

We should pick them off from a distance. I'm dropping in a few Hammer artillery bots for this purpose.
Make sure to keep enemy units from getting too close, they're not built for a stand-up fight!

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Transport") local commID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Commander") Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.LOAD_UNITS, {commID}, 0)

TriggerLogic.Message: Excellent work, Commander! We've made it!

You can move the camera in one of three ways: arrow keys, moving the cursor to the edge of screen, or holding down the middle mouse button and dragging.
Select your commander by left-clicking on him, or pressing Ctrl+C.
To order your commander to move somewhere, first select him, then right-click on the ground. You can also press M and left-click on the ground.
Orders can be queued by holding down SHIFT and issuing the orders.
Note that there are some places units cannot go, like steep hills.

Units will automatically fire on any enemy that comes within range. To attack a specific target, select the units to attack with and right-click on the enemy (or press A and left-click).
To have units stop to engage enemies while moving to a destination, issue a Fight order (press F, then left-click on the destination).
